# Versioning Strategy

## Overview
API/SDK evolution policy. API versioning (/v1/, /v2/). SDK semantic versioning. Deprecation timeline. Breaking change policy. Migration guides. Developers can plan for upgrades.

## Technical Approach
Document versioning approach for APIs and SDKs. Define deprecation policy (6 months notice). Provide migration guides between versions. Use semantic versioning for SDKs. Version prefix on API routes.

## User Stories

### US-001: Document API Versioning
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [5]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a developer, I want API versioning documented so that I can understand how APIs evolve.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- API versioning section created
- Explains: /v1/, /v2/ prefix approach
- Explains: version in headers
- Explains: when versions change
- Examples of versioned requests
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-002: Document SDK Semantic Versioning
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [5]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a developer, I want SDK versioning explained so that I can manage dependencies.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- SDK versioning section created
- Explains: semver (major.minor.patch)
- Explains: what constitutes major/minor/patch change
- Explains: compatibility guarantees
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-003: Define Deprecation Timeline
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [5]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a developer, I want deprecation timeline defined so that I know how long I have to migrate.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Deprecation policy section created
- 6 months notice for breaking changes
- 3 months notice for deprecations
- Deprecated endpoints marked in headers
- Examples of deprecation warnings
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-004: Document Breaking Change Policy
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [5]
